Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the macaroni.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and discard the core and seeds.

When boiling, stir the @macaroni{180%g} into the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the macaroni cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sliced pepper and @British pork mince{240%g}.

Fry until the mince has browned and the pepper has softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, heat your #grill{} to high. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the mince has browned, stir in the @smoked paprika{1%sachet}, @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and half the garlic. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{150%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @ciabatta{1}, then cut small zig zags into one edge of each half so they look like sharp teeth (use #scissors{} if easier).

Lay onto a #baking tray{}, cut-side up. Spread over the remaining @garlic clove{1}(minced) and drizzle with the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the garlic bread.

Grill until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

When the spooky sauce is ready, stir in the cooked macaroni and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Share the ghoulish goulash pasta between your #dishes{} and sprinkle over the remaining cheese.

Use the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} to draw a couple of eyes onto each monster garlic bread and serve on the side.

Enjoy!